## Sample Validator Adapter
```javascript
class TenantValidatorAdapter {
  constructor(tenantMeta) {
    this.issuer = tenantMeta.oidcIssuer || tenantMeta.samlIdpMetadata.issuer;
    this.audience = tenantMeta.allowedAudience;
    this.allowedBindings = new Set(tenantMeta.allowedBindings);
  }

  async validate(token, tenantMeta) {
    // Issuer validation
    if (token.iss !== this.issuer) {
      throw new ValidationError(`Invalid issuer: expected ${this.issuer}`);
    }

    // Audience validation
    if (!token.aud?.includes(this.audience)) {
      throw new ValidationError(`Invalid audience: expected ${this.audience}`);
    }

    // Binding validation
    if (!this.allowedBindings.has(token.binding_id)) {
      throw new ValidationError('Token binding not allowed for tenant');
    }

    return true;
  }
}
```

## Error Handling & Replay Protection

**Error Handling:**
- Standardize all errors to RFC 6749 error responses with `error` and `error_description`
- Tenant-specific errors masked to generic messages unless in trusted context
- Log full details server-side with correlation IDs

**Replay Protection:**
- Track JTI/nonce in distributed cache (Redis) with TTL matching token expiry
- Reject tokens already seen within the replay window
- For SAML, use `NotOnOrAfter` + `NotBefore` timing constraints

**Tenant Metadata Rotation:**
- Cache tenant metadata with short TTL (5 min default, configurable per tenant)
- Support push-based invalidation via webhook when IdP metadata changes
- Maintain versioning in cache keys for atomic updates
- Sign tenant metadata to detect tampering during rotation

## Architecture Considerations
- Use asymmetric keys for internal token signing per tenant or tenant group
- Implement token binding to client credentials where applicable
- Consider token downgrade attacks when exchanging from OIDC to SAML format

