Tests ability to design practical cache invalidation and explain trade-offs of Redis vs Memcached in a beginner context.

## Key Concepts

- cache-aside pattern
- tenant isolation in keys
- stampede mitigation with locks
- event-bus invalidation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudocode illustrating lazy reload with lock
async function getProduct(tid, pid) {
  const key = `tenant:${tid}:product:${pid}`
  let val = cache.get(key)
  if (val) return val
  const lock = `lock:${tid}:${pid}`
  if (redis.set(lock, 1, 'NX', 'PX', 1000)) {
    val = db.fetchProduct(tid, pid)
    cache.set(key, val, 300)
    redis.del(lock)
  } else {
    await sleep(50)
    return getProduct(tid, pid)
  }
  return val
}
```

