## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical cache-invalidation and per-tenant isolation using Redis/Memcached with simple locking to avoid stampedes. It also covers invalidation flows using tenant-scoped channels.

## Key Concepts
- Cache-aside pattern
- Per-tenant key namespaces and TTLs
- Invalidation via tenant-scoped channels/streams
- Lightweight distributed lock to prevent cache stampede

## Code Example
```javascript
// Get/Seed path (pseudo)
async function getProduct(tenantId, productId){
  const key = `tenant:${tenantId}:product:${productId}`
  let val = await cache.get(key)
  if (val) return JSON.parse(val)
  if (!acquireLock(key)) throw new Error('busy')
  try {
    val = await db.queryProduct(tenantId, productId)
    await cache.set(key, JSON.stringify(val), {ttl: tenantTTL(tenantId)})
    return val
  } finally { releaseLock(key) }
}
```
```javascript
