## Code Example
```javascript
class RideSaga {
  constructor(rideId, tenant) {
    this.rideId = rideId;
    this.tenant = tenant;
    this.state = 'RideCreated';
  }
  start() {
    publish({ type: 'RideCreated', rideId: this.rideId, tenant: this.tenant });
    this.next('ReserveDriver');
  }
  next(step) {
    // emit next step event
  }
  onEvent(e) {
    if (e.type === 'PaymentFailed') this.compensate('CollectPayment');
  }
  compensate(failedStep) {
    // issue compensations in reverse order
    publish({ type: 'Compensation', rideId: this.rideId, step: failedStep, tenant: this.tenant });
  }
}
``` 

## Follow-up Questions
- How to guarantee exactly-once delivery across regions?
- How to test sagas with replay and failure modes?
- How to evolve event schemas without breaking tenants?

